results.notes:
Fruiting from a deeply buried Douglas fir cone.
Cone buried approximately 1.2 inches beneath grass.
Carefully dug up the cone from side/beneath with fruiting bodies still attached. Harvested collection.
Carefully removed a section of “teeth”(dentinum) and mounted in Lugol’s and KOH on a glass slide.
Analysis of single dentinum with spores attached.
Spores: broadly ellipsoid to globose.
Amyloid in Lugol’s/KOH. Faintly warted/lumpy.
Small in size.
Dehydrated collection thoroughly and bagged for herbarium collection/genetic record.
